tellraw @s {"text":"\n-------------- Rauchergames Setup Guide --------------","color":"green"}
tellraw @s {"text":"\nLong Version:","color":"green"}
tellraw @s [{"text":"Overwiew: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Wokkagames (don't ask about the name) consists of, so far, 4 game modes (plus one for testing), that are all played with up to 12 players divided into 2 teams (while it is possible to play alone, at least 2 players per team are recommended). Each player can choose from one of 8 kits with unique stats and abilities. Win by completing the game mode-specific objective.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nStarting Out: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Make sure you have the ","color":"yellow"},{"text":"Wokka Resource Pack ","color":"gold","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to open link to Resource Pack"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"open_url","value":"https://github.com/flaviusmus/rauch_texturepack"}},{"text":"intalled. ","color":"yellow"},{"text":"If this is the first time the datapack is active, you wil be asked to set the lobby position. The lobby is the place players return to after a game. Move to the desired location, and click on the according text prompt (shows up when reloading) (","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/reload","color":"gold","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/reload"}},{"text":").","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nAdmins: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"To edit game settings, start games, add/remove maps etc. you need to be an admin. You can become an admin using the command (","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/tag NAME add admin","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/tag NAME add admin"},"color":"gold"},{"text":"). You can do this with every player you want, however they also need rights on the server (permission level 2 or more). To remove admin rights, do (","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/tag NAME remove admin","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/tag NAME remove admin"},"color":"gold"},{"text":"). Admins have access to the \"Settings\" Book in their first hotbar slot. From here you can change game modes, maps and more.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nAdding a Map: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"In order to play, at least one map must exist. You can spawn a prebuilt map by going to the 3rd page of the \"Settings\" Book and clicking on \"Spawn prebuilt Map\". This method automatically sets up everything. To add a custom map, click \"Add Map\" instead. A Guide will be available there.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nKits: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Before starting, each player has to select a kit using the book called \"Kit Selector / Settings\". You can see their stats and abilities by hovering over the name. Click to select. Each class has three abilities, R, Q and F. In game, you can activate R by right-clicking and Q and F by pressing the respective key on your keyboard. Abilities usually have a time-based cooldown.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nGame Modes: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"You can choose a game mode using the \"Settings\" Book. Hovering over the name will show information about the mode.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nStarting a Game: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"After having selected a kit and a map (using the 2nd page of the \"Settings\" Book), right click with the green item called \"Join Queue\" to join the queue. Here all players can choose a team (players that don't pick will be evenly distributed). Note that there is nothing (except evil admins and/or your friendship) preventing unbalanced teams (like a 3v1). Admins can start the game using either the chosen teams or random teams. Make sure everyone that wants to play is in queue before starting.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nUtility Functions (feat. Aborting Games): ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Players with rights on the server can use helpful utility functions, just type ","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/function utils_rauch","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/function utils_rauch"},"color":"gold"},{"text":" and the functions should be available via auto-complete. The names of the functions should be self-explanatory.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s {"text":"\nShort Version:","color":"green"}
tellraw @s [{"text":"1. Make sure you have the Resource Pack installed","color":"yellow"},{"text":" (link)","color":"gold","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to open link to Resource Pack"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"open_url","value":"https://github.com/flaviusmus/rauch_texturepack"}}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"2. Set Lobby Position (Text Prompt)","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"3. Type ","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/tag ","color":"gold","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/tag @s add admin"}},{"selector":"@s","color":"gold","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/tag @s add admin"}},{"text":" add admin","color":"gold","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/tag @s add admin"}},{"text":" to become an admin","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"4. Spawn a prebuilt map (3rd page of \"Settings\" Book)","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"5. Select a map (2nd page of \"Settings\" Book)","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"6. Select a game mode (1st page of \"Settings\" Book)","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"7. Everyone has to select a kit and join the queue","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"8. An admin has to start the game","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s {"text":"------------------- Setup Guide End -------------------","color":"green"}
